:: History of open source {"position":"300,1075","size":"100,100"}
open source was started in academics when people wouid share software freely. It became an offical thing in the 1980's to help combat proprietary software.  The name Open Souce became offical in 1998.

Now open source has become so large that it powers many things from phones and smart watches to major servers



