:: What bad has come from open source {"position":"675,1275","size":"100,100"}
Open source can have drawbacks like security risks if projects aren’t well maintained, lack of consistent support or updates, and compatibility issues between versions. It can also be difficult for beginners, has no guaranteed accountability, and may vary in quality since anyone can contribute.

[[what is open source]]



:: What good has open source done {"position":"900,600","size":"100,100"}
Open source speeds up innovation by letting people share and reuse code. It improves security through public review, helps learners study real-world code, reduces reliance on single companies, and results in more reliable and customizable software.


[[what is open source]]

 


:: Why is open source important {"position":"950,975","size":"100,100"}
